    <TD height="44" width="594">
      <p align="center"><font face="Arial" size="4">Super Remote</font></TD>
        </TR>
  <TR>
    <TD height="194" width="594">

      <p align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial; ">
      <font size="4">Introduction:</font></span></p>

      <p align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial">SUPER Remote&nbsp; 
      actually is a simplified Communication Server in real virtual classroom 
      system. It could connect with multiple instances of you component and 
      broadcast received message so components could talk with each other 
      indeed. </span></p>

      <p align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial"><font size="4">Download:</font></span></p>

      <blockquote>

      <p align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial">
      <a href="SuperRemote.zip">SuperRemote.zip</a></span></p>

      </blockquote>

      <p><span style="font-family: Arial"><font size="4">How to use it?</font></span></p>

      <p><span style="font-family: Arial">It is a stand alone executable file on 
      Windows OS, just like normal virtual remote The only difference is that it 
      could connect up to 5 servers. </span></p>

      <p><span style="font-family: Arial">Click to run, you will see:</span></p>

      <p align="center">
      <img border="0" src="Figure1.JPG" width="480" height="465"></p>

      <p align="center"><span style="font-family: Arial">Figure 1 Super Remote 
      Control</span></p>

      <p><span style="font-family: Arial">It will relay all received messages 
      between all connected servers. For example, the message shown in Figure1 
      was sent by super remote, the responses of connected servers are shown in 
      following two figures:</span></p>

      <p align="center">
      <img border="0" src="Figure2.JPG" width="340" height="403"></p>

      <p align="center">Figure 2 One Server on Local Machine</p>

      <p align="center">
      <img border="0" src="Figure3.JPG" width="256" height="313"></p>

      <p align="center">Figure 3 One Server on Remote Machine </p>

      <p align="left"><span style="font-family: Arial">Using super remote, 
      multiple instance of your component could be hooked up together. Finally, 
      student tool and teacher tool could also join the connection.</span></p>

      <HR color="#808080">

